The latest stable MSTest is **4.2.3** — a major version jump from 3.8.0. Here are the breaking changes relevant to your code and project:

### 🔴 Breaking: `[ExpectedException]` removed in v4

Your two test methods use `[ExpectedException]`, which was removed. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

### Other v4 breaking changes (not hitting your code today, but good to know)

| Change | Impact |
|---|---|
| `Assert` APIs no longer accept `message` + `params object[]` — use string interpolation | Low — you don't use message params |
| `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` | Only if you have custom test method attributes |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Only if you use `ClassCleanup(ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass)` |
| `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>` | Only if you call `.Contains()` (→ `.ContainsKey()`) |
| `TestTimeout` enum removed | Use `int.MaxValue` instead of `TestTimeout.Infinite` |
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| Dropped .NET < 8 support | You're on net8.0, so fine |
